{"matches":[{"vulnerability":{"id":"GHSA-6xvm-j4wr-6v98","dataSource":"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-6xvm-j4wr-6v98","namespace":"github:language:rust","severity":"High","urls":["https://github.com/quinn-rs/quinn/security/advisories/GHSA-6xvm-j4wr-6v98","https://github.com/quinn-rs/quinn/pull/2559","https://rustsec.org/advisories/RUSTSEC-2026-0037.html","https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-31812"],"description":"Quinn affected by unauthenticated remote DoS via panic in QUIC transport parameter parsing","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N","metrics":{"baseScore":8.7},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-31812","epss":0.00162,"percentile":0.37128,"date":"2026-04-10"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-31812","cwe":"CWE-248","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Primary"}],"fix":{"versions":["0.11.14"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"0.11.14","date":"2026-03-11","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.13122},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2026-31812","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-31812","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"High","urls":["https://github.com/quinn-rs/quinn/security/advisories/GHSA-6xvm-j4wr-6v98"],"description":"Quinn is a pure-Rust, async-compatible implementation of the IETF QUIC transport protocol. Prior to 0.11.14, a remote, unauthenticated attacker can trigger a denial of service in applications using vulnerable quinn versions by sending a crafted QUIC Initial packet containing malformed quic_transport_parameters. In quinn-proto parsing logic, attacker-controlled varints are decoded with unwrap(), so truncated encodings cause Err(UnexpectedEnd) and panic. This is reachable over the network with a single packet and no prior trust or authentication. This vulnerability is fixed in 0.11.14.","cvss":[{"source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:X/CR:X/IR:X/AR:X/MAV:X/MAC:X/MAT:X/MPR:X/MUI:X/MVC:X/MVI:X/MVA:X/MSC:X/MSI:X/MSA:X/S:X/AU:X/R:X/V:X/RE:X/U:X","metrics":{"baseScore":8.7},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-31812","epss":0.00162,"percentile":0.37128,"date":"2026-04-10"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-31812","cwe":"CWE-248","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Primary"}]}],"matchDetails":[{"type":"exact-direct-match","matcher":"rust-matcher","searchedBy":{"language":"rust","namespace":"github:language:rust","package":{"name":"quinn-proto","version":"0.11.13"}},"found":{"vulnerabilityID":"GHSA-6xvm-j4wr-6v98","versionConstraint":"<0.11.14 (unknown)"},"fix":{"suggestedVersion":"0.11.14"}}],"artifact":{"id":"f13b30e907cb565e","name":"quinn-proto","version":"0.11.13","type":"rust-crate","locations":[{"path":"/packages/desktop/src-tauri/Cargo.lock","accessPath":"/packages/desktop/src-tauri/Cargo.lock","annotations":{"evidence":"primary"}}],"language":"rust","licenses":[],"cpes":["cpe:2.3:a:quinn-proto:quinn-proto:0.11.13:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:quinn-proto:quinn_proto:0.11.13:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:quinn_proto:quinn-proto:0.11.13:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:quinn_proto:quinn_proto:0.11.13:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:quinn:quinn-proto:0.11.13:*:*:*:*:*:*:*","cpe:2.3:a:quinn:quinn_proto:0.11.13:*:*:*:*:*:*:*"],"purl":"pkg:cargo/quinn-proto@0.11.13","upstreams":[]}},{"vulnerability":{"id":"GHSA-434x-w66g-qw3r","dataSource":"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-434x-w66g-qw3r","namespace":"github:language:rust","severity":"Medium","urls":["https://github.com/tokio-rs/bytes/security/advisories/GHSA-434x-w66g-qw3r","https://github.com/tokio-rs/bytes/commit/d0293b0e35838123c51ca5dfdf468ecafee4398f","https://github.com/tokio-rs/bytes/releases/tag/v1.11.1","https://rustsec.org/advisories/RUSTSEC-2026-0007.html","https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-25541"],"description":"bytes has integer overflow in BytesMut::reserve","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:P","metrics":{"baseScore":5.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-25541","epss":0.00019,"percentile":0.04901,"date":"2026-04-10"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2026-25541","cwe":"CWE-680","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Primary"}],"fix":{"versions":["1.11.1"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"1.11.1","date":"2026-02-04","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.009975000000000001},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2026-25541","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-25541","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"High","urls":["https://github.com/tokio-rs/bytes/commit/d0293b0e35838123c51ca5dfdf468ecafee4398f","https://github.com/tokio-rs/bytes/releases/tag/v1.11.1","https://github.com/tokio-rs/bytes/security/advisories/GHSA-434x-w66g-qw3r","https://rustsec.org/advisories/RUSTSEC-2026-0007.html"],"description":"Bytes is a utility library for working with bytes. From version 1.2.1 to before 1.11.1, Bytes is vulnerable to integer overflow in BytesMut::reserve. In the unique reclaim path of BytesMut::reserve, if the condition \"v_capacity >= new_cap + offset\" uses an unchecked addition. When new_cap + offset overflows usize in release builds, this condition may incorrectly pass, causing self.cap to be set to a value that exceeds the actual allocated capacity. Subsequent APIs such as spare_capacity_mut() then trust this corrupted cap value and may create out-of-bounds slices, leading to UB. This behavior is observable in release builds (integer overflow wraps), whereas debug builds panic due to overflow checks. This issue has been patched in version 1.11.1.","cvss":[{"source":"nvd@nist.gov","type":"Primary","version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H","metrics":{"baseScore":7.5,"exploitabilityScore":3.9,"impactScore":3.6},"vendorMetadata":{}},{"source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Seco